Jean-Claude Trichet: Let us carry this noble endeavour further by giving Europe now and for the longer term the institutions it deserves.
Jean-Claude Trichet: We have proved that our single currency is stable and credible, preserving price stability over time.
Jean-Claude Trichet: We have combined political freedom with economic freedom and social peace.
Jean-Claude Trichet: We have replaced confrontation and conflict with cooperation and consensus.
Jean-Claude Trichet: Europe is in the vanguard of nations working peacefully together
Jean-Claude Trichet: It is vital that all nations engage fully in the European historical endeavour and look with confidence to the future.
Jean-Claude Trichet: In this Union of tomorrow, would it be too bold to envisage a ministry of Finance of the Union?
Jean-Claude Trichet: We could then give euro area authorities much deeper and authoritative say in the country’s economic policies
Jean-Claude Trichet: But if a country is still not delivering, I think all would agree that the second stage has to be different.
Jean-Claude Trichet: As a first stage, it is justified to provide financial assistance in the context of a strong adjustment programme.
Jean-Claude Trichet: In my view, it could be appropriate to foresee for the medium term two stages for countries in difficulty.
Trichet: Looking at euro area today, we see clearly that countries that abide by the rules of the single currency can thrive and prosper.
Jean-Claude Trichet: EMU has brought growth, fostered trade, brought employment and price stability. There is no crisis of the euro.
Jean-Claude Trichet: "Confronting the challenges of the future requires strengthening the institutions of economic union – the E in EMU"
